720558f-a.title: Manhattan: Hudson Street - Grove Street
720558f-a.folder: Hudson Street & Grove Street, Manhattan, NY

720559f-b.title: Manhattan: Hudson Street - Grove Street
720559f-b.text:
(1)
Pudson Street, east side, north from and including Grove, to and in-
cluding Christopher Streets, as seen from the U.S. Appraises Stores, and
showing a general view eastward. Prominent buildings are (left to
right), the Chrysler, N.Y. Life, Metropolitan Life and the Consolidated
Gas Co. Note Public School No. 3, at the N.E. corner of Grove Street.
July 25, 1930.
P. L. Sperr.
(2)
The same, from a different angle.
July 25, 1930.
P. L. Sperr.

720560f-a.title: Manhattan: Hudson Street - Grove Street.
720560f-a.text:
Hudson Street, west side, at Grove Street,
showing St. Lukes P.E. 2hapel; cornerstone laid
June 4, 1821. To the right are 3 story structures
that extend to Christopher Street. The parsh house
is the first of these, occupying a doube frontage.
This photo was reproduced on page 96 of the published
volume "Changing New York."
Juune 18, 1936
Berenice Abbott, photo
Federal Art Project
